The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 May is 42,083 (4,870.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 May, there were 106 new confirmed cases (12.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 April, there were 138 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (32 fewer cases).
